          h1 FBAR
          h2 Report of Foreign Bank and Financial Accounts
          button.btn.btn-question Question?

        .col-xs-6.content.right
          p FBAR, or Report of Foreign Bank and Financial Accounts, is the name of a form that is used to disclose foreign financial accounts to the IRS.
          p It must be filed electronically through FinCEN's BSA E-Filing System by June 30th of every year.
          p Proper preparation is key to the FBAR filing because penalties associated with failure to comply with the reporting requirements can be significant.


